fields.name: Inception
fields.description:
A thief who steals corporate secrets through the use of dream-sharing technology is given the inverse task of planting an idea into the mind of a C.E.O. |
Director - Christopher Nolan |
Starring - Leonardo DiCaprio, Joseph Gordon-Levitt, Elliot Page, Tom Hardy

fields.name: Metropolis
fields.description: In a futuristic city sharply divided between the working class and the city planners, the son of the city's mastermind falls in love with a working class prophet who predicts the coming of a savior to mediate their differences. | Director - Fritz Lang | Starring - Alfred Abel, Gustav Fröhlich, Rudolf Klein-Rogge, Fritz Rasp

fields.name: Circus
fields.description: The Tramp finds work and the girl of his dreams at a circus. | Director - Charles Chaplin

fields.name: Broadway Melody of 1929
fields.description: A pair of sisters from the vaudeville circuit try to make it big time on Broadway, but matters of the heart complicate the attempt. | Director - Harry Beaumont

fields.name: Girl I loved
fields.description: John Middleton is distressed to learn that his family is taking in an orphan girl named Mary. He turns aside all her attempts to befriend him. But with the passage of time, John discovers... | Director - Joseph De Grasse

fields.name: Gone with the Wind
fields.description: A manipulative woman and a roguish man conduct a turbulent romance during the American Civil War and Reconstruction periods. | Director - Victor Fleming, George Cukor, Sam Wood | Starring - Thomas Mitchell, Barbara O'Neil, Vivien Leigh, Evelyn Keyes

fields.name: Gone with the Wind
fields.description: A manipulative woman and a roguish man conduct a turbulent romance during the American Civil War and Reconstruction periods.

fields.name: Mr. Smith Goes To Washington
fields.description: A naive man is appointed to fill a vacancy in the United States Senate. His plans promptly collide with political corruption, but he doesn't back down. | Director - Frank Capra

fields.name: Snow White and the Seven Dwarfs
fields.description: Exiled into the dangerous forest by her wicked stepmother, a princess is rescued by seven dwarf miners who make her part of their household. | Director - William Cottrell, David Hand, Wilfred Jackson, Larry Morey, Perce Pearce, Ben Sharpsteen

fields.name: Wizard of Oz
fields.description: Dorothy Gale is swept away from a farm in Kansas to a magical land of Oz in a tornado and embarks on a quest with her new friends to see the Wizard who can help her return home to Kansas and help her friends as well. | Directors - Victor Fleming, George Cukor

fields.name: Modern Times
fields.description: The Tramp struggles to live in modern industrial society with the help of a young homeless woman. | Director - Charles Chaplin

fields.name: Pinocchio
fields.description: A living puppet, with the help of a cricket as his conscience, must prove himself worthy to become a real boy. | Directors - Norman Ferguson, T. Hee, Wilfred Jackson, Jack Kinney, Hamilton Luske, Bill Roberts, Ben Sharpsteen

fields.name: Dumbo
fields.description: Ridiculed because of his enormous ears, a young circus elephant is assisted by a mouse to achieve his full potential. | Directors - Samuel Armstrong, Norman Ferguson, Wilfred Jackson, Jack Kinney, Bill Roberts, Ben Sharpsteen, John Elliotte

fields.name: Suspicion
fields.description: A shy young heiress marries a charming gentleman, and soon begins to suspect he is planning to murder her. | Director - Alfred Hitchcock

fields.name: Gilda
fields.description: A small-time gambler hired to work in a Buenos Aires casino discovers his employer's new wife is his former lover. | Director - Charles Vidor | Starring - Rita Hayworth, Glenn Ford, George Macready, Joseph Calleia

fields.name: Lady and the Monster
fields.description: A millionaire's brain is preserved after his death, and telepathically begins to take control of those around him. | Director - George Sherman

fields.name: Bambi
fields.description: The story of a young deer growing up in the forest. | Directors - James Algar, Samuel Armstrong, David Hand, Graham Heid, Bill Roberts, Paul Satterfield, Norman Wright, Arthur Davis, Clyde Geronimi

fields.name: Casablanca
fields.description: A cynical American expatriate struggles to decide whether or not he should help his former lover and her fugitive husband escape French Morocco. | Director - Michael Curtiz

fields.name: Mark Of Zorro
fields.description: A young Spanish aristocrat must masquerade as a fop in order to maintain his secret identity of Zorro as he restores justice to early California. | Director - Rouben Mamoulian

fields.name: For Whom The Bell Tolls
fields.description: During the Spanish Civil War, an American allied with the Republicans finds romance during a desperate mission to blow up a strategically important bridge. | Director - Sam Wood | Starring - Gary Cooper, Ingrid Bergman

fields.name: Saigon
fields.description: After WW2, two army buddies, one of them terminally-ill, embark on a series of adventures in South-East Asia and run across a dangerous criminal and his pretty secretary. | Director - Leslie Fenton

fields.name: Attack of the 50 Foot Woman
fields.description: When an abused socialite grows to giant size because of an alien encounter and an aborted murder attempt, she goes after her cheating husband with revenge on her mind. | Director - Nathan Juran

fields.name: War Of The Worlds
fields.description: A small town in California is attacked by Martians, beginning a worldwide invasion. | Director - Byron Haskin

fields.name: Attack of the Crab Monsters
fields.description: Scientists become trapped on a shrinking island with intelligent, murderous giant crabs. | Director - Roger Corman

fields.name: Searchers
fields.description: An American Civil War veteran embarks on a journey to rescue his niece from the Comanches. | Stars - John Wayne

fields.name: Ben-Hur
fields.description: After a Jewish prince is betrayed and sent into slavery by a Roman friend, he regains his freedom and comes back for revenge. | Starring - Charlton Heston, Jack Hawkins, Haya Harareet, Stephen Boyd

fields.name: Alice in Wonderland
fields.description:
Alice stumbles into the world of Wonderland. Will she get home? Not if the Queen of Hearts has her way.
| Director - Clyde Geronimi, Wilfred Jackson, Hamilton Luske, Jack Kinney

fields.name: Bridge on the River Kwai
fields.description: British POWs are forced to build a railway bridge across the river Kwai for their Japanese captors, not knowing that the allied forces are planning to destroy it. | Director - David Lean | Starring - William Holden, Alec Guinness

fields.name: Journey to the Center of the Earth
fields.description: An Edinburgh professor and assorted colleagues follow an explorer's trail down an extinct Icelandic volcano to the earth's center. | Director - Henry Levin

fields.name: Peter Pan
fields.description: Wendy and her brothers are whisked away to the magical world of Neverland with the hero of their stories, Peter Pan. | Directors - Clyde Geronimi, Wilfred Jackson, Hamilton Luske, Jack Kinney

fields.name: Around The World In 80 Days
fields.description: A Victorian Englishman bets that with the new steamships and railways he can circumnavigate the globe in eighty days. | Directors - Michael Anderson, John Farrow

fields.name: Some Like It Hot
fields.description: After two male musicians witness a mob hit, they flee the state in an all-female band disguised as women, but further complications set in. | Starring - Marilyn Monroe, Tony Curtis, Jack Lemmon

fields.name: Sleeping Beauty
fields.description: After being snubbed by the royal family, a malevolent fairy places a curse on a princess which only a prince can break, along with the help of three good fairies. | Directors - Clyde Geronimi, Les Clark, Hamilton Luske, Wolfgang Reitherman

fields.name: Thunderball
fields.description: James Bond heads to the Bahamas to recover two nuclear warheads stolen by S.P.E.C.T.R.E. Agent Emilio Largo in an international extortion scheme. | Director -Terence Young | Starring - Sean Connery

fields.name: 2001: A Space Odyssey
fields.description: After discovering a mysterious artifact buried beneath the Lunar surface, mankind sets off on a quest to find its origins with help from intelligent supercomputer H.A.L. 9000. | Director - Stanley Kubrick

fields.name: Cool Hand Luke
fields.description: A laid back Southern man is sentenced to two years in a rural prison, but refuses to conform. | Starring - Paul Newman

fields.name: Goldfinger
fields.description: While investigating a gold magnate's smuggling, James Bond uncovers a plot to contaminate the Fort Knox gold reserve. | Starring - Sean Connery, Gert Fröbe

fields.name: Birds
fields.description: A wealthy San Francisco socialite pursues a potential boyfriend to a small Northern California town that slowly takes a turn for the bizarre when birds of all kinds suddenly begin to attack people. | Director - Alfred Hitchcock

fields.name: Astro Zombies
fields.description: The Plan - to build a super human; How? - by murdering innocent convenient victims and using various bits of them; The Result - Creatures on the rampage. | Director - Ted V. Mikels

fields.name: Star Wars
fields.description: A long time ago in a galaxy far, far away...

fields.name: Alien
fields.description: After a space merchant vessel receives an unknown transmission as a distress call, one of the crew is attacked by a mysterious life form and they soon realize that its life cycle has merely begun.

fields.name: Taxi Driver
fields.description: A mentally unstable veteran works as a nighttime taxi driver in New York City, where the perceived decadence and sleaze fuels his urge for violent action by attempting to liberate a presidential campaign worker and an underage prostitute.

fields.name: Grease
fields.description: Good girl Sandy Olsson and greaser Danny Zuko fell in love over the summer. When they unexpectedly discover they're now in the same high school, will they be able to rekindle their romance?

fields.name: One Flew Over the Cuckoo’s Nest
fields.description: A criminal pleads insanity and is admitted to a mental institution, where he rebels against the oppressive nurse and rallies up the scared patients.

fields.name: Godfather
fields.description: The aging patriarch of an organized crime dynasty transfers control of his clandestine empire to his reluctant son.

fields.name: Godfather: Part II
fields.description: The early life and career of Vito Corleone in 1920s New York City is portrayed, while his son, Michael, expands and tightens his grip on the family crime syndicate.

fields.name: Jaws
fields.description: When a killer shark unleashes chaos on a beach community, it's up to a local sheriff, a marine biologist, and an old seafarer to hunt the beast down.

fields.name: Towering Inferno
fields.description: At the opening party of a colossal, but poorly constructed, office building, a massive fire breaks out that threatens to destroy the tower and everyone in it.

fields.name: Star Trek: The Motion Picture
fields.description: When an alien spacecraft of enormous power is spotted approaching Earth, Admiral James T. Kirk resumes command of the overhauled USS Enterprise in order to intercept it.

fields.name: Star Wars: Revenge of the Jedi
fields.description: The saga continues.

fields.name: Star Wars: Episode V - The Empire Strikes Back
fields.description: After the Rebels are brutally overpowered by the Empire on the ice planet Hoth, Luke Skywalker begins Jedi training with Yoda, while his friends are pursued by Darth Vader and a bounty hunter named Boba Fett all over the galaxy.

fields.name: Predator
fields.description: A team of commandos on a mission in a Central American jungle find themselves hunted by an extraterrestrial warrior.

fields.name: Gremlins
fields.description: A boy inadvertently breaks three important rules concerning his new pet and unleashes a horde of malevolently mischievous monsters on a small town.

fields.name: Raiders of the Lost Ark
fields.description: In 1936, archaeologist and adventurer Indiana Jones is hired by the U.S. government to find the Ark of the Covenant before Adolf Hitler's Nazis can obtain its awesome powers.

fields.name: Scarface
fields.description: In 1980 Miami, a determined Cuban immigrant takes over a drug cartel and succumbs to greed.

fields.name: Batman
fields.description: The Dark Knight of Gotham City begins his war on crime with his first major enemy being Jack Napier, a criminal who becomes the clownishly homicidal Joker.

fields.name: Conan the Barbarian
fields.description: A young boy, Conan, becomes a slave after his parents are killed and tribe destroyed by a savage warlord and sorcerer, Thulsa Doom. When he grows up he becomes a fearless, invincible fighter. Set free, he plots revenge against Thulsa Doom.

fields.name: E.T. THE EXTRA-TERRESTRIAL
fields.description: A troubled child summons the courage to help a friendly alien escape Earth and return to his home world.

fields.name: Rambo
fields.description: A veteran Green Beret is forced by a cruel Sheriff and his deputies to flee into the mountains and wage an escalating one-man war against his pursuers.

fields.name: View to a Kill
fields.description: The recovery of a microchip off the body of a fellow agent, leads James Bond to a mad industrialist who plans to create a worldwide microchip monopoly by destroying California's Silicon Valley.

fields.name: Mad Max Beyond Thunderdome
fields.description: After being exiled from the most advanced town in post apocalyptic Australia, a drifter travels with a group of abandoned children to rebel against the town's queen.

fields.name: Reservoir Dogs
fields.description: When a simple jewelry heist goes horribly wrong, the surviving criminals begin to suspect that one of them is a police informant.

fields.name: Titanic
fields.description: A seventeen-year-old aristocrat falls in love with a kind but poor artist aboard the luxurious, ill-fated R.M.S. Titanic.

fields.name: Star Wars: Episode I - The Phantom Menace
fields.description: Two Jedi escape a hostile blockade to find allies and come across a young boy who may bring balance to the Force, but the long dormant Sith resurface to claim their original glory.

fields.name: Goodfellas
fields.description: The story of Henry Hill and his life in the mob, covering his relationship with his wife Karen Hill and his mob partners Jimmy Conway and Tommy DeVito in the Italian-American crime syndicate.

fields.name: Fight Club
fields.description: An insomniac office worker and a devil-may-care soapmaker form an underground fight club that evolves into something much, much more.

fields.name: Saving Private Ryan
fields.description: Following the Normandy Landings, a group of U.S. soldiers go behind enemy lines to retrieve a paratrooper whose brothers have been killed in action.

fields.name: Lost World: Jurassic Park
fields.description: A research team is sent to the Jurassic Park Site B island to study the dinosaurs there, while an InGen team approaches with another agenda.

fields.name: Good Will Hunting
fields.description: Will Hunting, a janitor at M.I.T., has a gift for mathematics, but needs help from a psychologist to find direction in his life.

fields.name: Fifth Element
fields.description: In the colorful future, a cab driver unwittingly becomes the central figure in the search for a legendary cosmic weapon to keep Evil and Mr. Zorg at bay.

fields.name: Blair Witch Project
fields.description: Three film students vanish after traveling into a Maryland forest to film a documentary on the local Blair Witch legend, leaving only their footage behind.

fields.name: Schindler’s List
fields.description: In German-occupied Poland during World War II, industrialist Oskar Schindler gradually becomes concerned for his Jewish workforce after witnessing their persecution by the Nazis.

fields.name: Matrix
fields.description: When a beautiful stranger leads computer hacker Neo to a forbidding underworld, he discovers the shocking truth--the life he knows is the elaborate deception of an evil cyber-intelligence.

fields.name: Seven
fields.description: Two detectives, a rookie and a veteran, hunt a serial killer who uses the seven deadly sins as his motives.

fields.name: American Beauty
fields.description: A sexually frustrated suburban father has a mid-life crisis after becoming infatuated with his daughter's best friend.

fields.name: American History X
fields.description: A former neo-nazi skinhead tries to prevent his younger brother from going down the same wrong path that he did.

fields.name: Dark Knight
fields.description: When the menace known as the Joker wreaks havoc and chaos on the people of Gotham, Batman must accept one of the greatest psychological and physical tests of his ability to fight injustice.

fields.name: Lord of the Rings: The Fellowship of the Ring
fields.description: A meek Hobbit from the Shire and eight companions set out on a journey to destroy the powerful One Ring and save Middle-earth from the Dark Lord Sauron.

fields.name: Star Wars: Episode III - Revenge Of The Sith
fields.description: Three years into the Clone Wars, the Jedi rescue Palpatine from Count Dooku. As Obi-Wan pursues a new threat, Anakin acts as a double agent between the Jedi Council and Palpatine and is lured into a sinister plan to rule the galaxy.

fields.name: Avatar
fields.description: A paraplegic Marine dispatched to the moon Pandora on a unique mission becomes torn between following his orders and protecting the world he feels is his home.

fields.name: Gladiator
fields.description: A former Roman General sets out to exact vengeance against the corrupt emperor who murdered his family and sent him into slavery.

fields.name: Watchmen
fields.description: In 1985 where former superheroes exist, the murder of a colleague sends active vigilante Rorschach into his own sprawling investigation, uncovering something that could completely change the course of history as we know it.

fields.name: Star Wars: Episode II - Attack Of The Clones
fields.description: Ten years after initially meeting, Anakin Skywalker shares a forbidden romance with Padmé Amidala, while Obi-Wan Kenobi investigates an assassination attempt on the senator and discovers a secret clone army crafted for the Jedi.

fields.name: Pianist
fields.description: A Polish Jewish musician struggles to survive the destruction of the Warsaw ghetto of World War II.

fields.name: Sin City
fields.description: A movie that explores the dark and miserable town, Basin City, tells the story of three different people, all caught up in violent corruption.

fields.name: Hannibal
fields.description: Living in exile, Dr. Hannibal Lecter tries to reconnect with now disgraced F.B.I. Agent Clarice Starling, and finds himself a target for revenge from a powerful victim.

fields.name: Friday the 13th
fields.description: A group of young adults visit a boarded up campsite named Crystal Lake where they soon encounter the mysterious Jason Voorhees and his deadly intentions.

fields.name: Batman Begins
fields.description: After training with his mentor, Batman begins his fight to free crime-ridden Gotham City from corruption.

fields.name: V For Vendetta
fields.description: In a future British tyranny, a shadowy freedom fighter, known only by the alias of "V", plots to overthrow it with the help of a young woman.

fields.name: Joker
fields.description: In Gotham City, mentally troubled comedian Arthur Fleck is disregarded and mistreated by society. He then embarks on a downward spiral of revolution and bloody crime. This path brings him face-to-face with his alter-ego: the Joker.

fields.name: Star Wars: Episode IX - Rise of Skywalker
fields.description: The surviving members of the resistance face the First Order once again, and the legendary conflict between the Jedi and the Sith reaches its peak bringing the Skywalker saga to its end.

fields.name: Once Upon a Time in Hollywood
fields.description: A faded television actor and his stunt double strive to achieve fame and success in the final years of Hollywood's Golden Age in 1969 Los Angeles.

fields.name: Rogue One: A Star Wars Story
fields.description: The daughter of an Imperial scientist joins the Rebel Alliance in a risky move to steal the plans for the Death Star.

fields.name: Mad Max: Fury Road
fields.description: In a post-apocalyptic wasteland, a woman rebels against a tyrannical ruler in search for her homeland with the aid of a group of female prisoners, a psychotic worshiper, and a drifter named Max.

fields.name: Skyfall
fields.description: James Bond's loyalty to M is tested when her past comes back to haunt her. When MI6 comes under attack, 007 must track down and destroy the threat, no matter how personal the cost.

fields.name: Ford V Ferrari
fields.description: American car designer Carroll Shelby and driver Ken Miles battle corporate interference and the laws of physics to build a revolutionary race car for Ford in order to defeat Ferrari at the 24 Hours of Le Mans in 1966.

fields.name: Black Panther
fields.description: T'Challa, heir to the hidden but advanced kingdom of Wakanda, must step forward to lead his people into a new future and must confront a challenger from his country's past. RIP Chadwick Boseman

fields.name: Her
fields.description: In a near future, a lonely writer develops an unlikely relationship with an operating system designed to meet his every need.

fields.name: It
fields.description: In the summer of 1989, a group of bullied kids band together to destroy a shape-shifting monster, which disguises itself as a clown and preys on the children of Derry, their small Maine town.

fields.name: Harry Potter and the Deathly Hallows: Part Two
fields.description: Harry, Ron, and Hermione search for Voldemort's remaining Horcruxes in their effort to destroy the Dark Lord as the final battle rages on at Hogwarts.

fields.name: Django Unchained
fields.description: With the help of a German bounty hunter, a freed slave sets out to rescue his wife from a brutal Mississippi plantation owner.

fields.name: Iron Man
fields.description: After being held captive in an Afghan cave, billionaire engineer Tony Stark creates a unique weaponized suit of armor to fight evil.

fields.name: Tenet
fields.description: Armed with only one word, Tenet, and fighting for the survival of the entire world, a Protagonist journeys through a twilight world of international espionage on a mission that will unfold in something beyond real time.

fields.name: Heat
fields.description: A group of professional bank robbers start to feel the heat from police when they unknowingly leave a clue at their latest heist.

fields.name: No Time to Die
fields.description: James Bond has left active service. His peace is short-lived when Felix Leiter, an old friend from the CIA, turns up asking for help, leading Bond onto the trail of a mysterious villain armed with dangerous new technology.

fields.name: Rocketeer
fields.description: A young pilot stumbles onto a prototype jetpack that allows him to become a high-flying masked hero.

fields.name: Bad Boys
fields.description: Two hip detectives protect a witness to a murder while investigating a case of stolen heroin from the evidence storage room from their police precinct.

fields.name: Blade
fields.description: A half-vampire, half-mortal man becomes a protector of the mortal race, while slaying evil vampires.

fields.name: 2 Fast 2 Furious
fields.description: Former cop Brian O'Conner is called upon to bust a dangerous criminal and he recruits the help of a former childhood friend and street racer who has a chance to redeem himself.

fields.name: Total Recall
fields.description: When a man goes for virtual vacation memories of the planet Mars, an unexpected and harrowing series of events forces him to go to the planet for real - or is he?

fields.name: Independence Day
fields.description: The aliens are coming and their goal is to invade and destroy Earth. Fighting superior technology, mankind's best weapon is the will to survive.

fields.name: Matrix Reloaded
fields.description: Freedom fighters Neo, Trinity and Morpheus continue to lead the revolt against the Machine Army, unleashing their arsenal of extraordinary skills and weaponry against the systematic forces of repression and exploitation.

fields.name: Black Widow
fields.description: A film about Natasha Romanoff in her quests between the films Civil War and Infinity War.

fields.name: Back to the Future
fields.description: Marty McFly, a 17-year-old high school student, is accidentally sent thirty years into the past in a time-traveling DeLorean invented by his close friend, the eccentric scientist Doc Brown.

fields.name: Teenage Mutant Ninja Turtles
fields.description: Four teenage mutant ninja turtles emerge from the shadows to protect New York City from a gang of criminal ninjas.

fields.name: Aliens
fields.description: Fifty-seven years after surviving an apocalyptic attack aboard her space vessel by merciless space creatures, Officer Ripley awakens from hyper-sleep and tries to warn anyone who will listen about the predators.

fields.name: Back To The Future 2
fields.description: After visiting 2015, Marty McFly must repeat his visit to 1955 to prevent disastrous changes to 1985...without interfering with his first trip.

fields.name: Spaceballs
fields.description: A star pilot and his sidekick must come to the rescue of a Princess and save the galaxy from a ruthless race of beings known as Spaceballs.

fields.name: Space Jam
fields.description: In a desperate attempt to win a basketball match and earn their freedom, the Looney Tunes seek the aid of retired basketball champion, Michael Jordan.

fields.name: Toy Story
fields.description: A cowboy doll is profoundly threatened and jealous when a new spaceman figure supplants him as top toy in a boy's room.

fields.name: Quantum Of Solace
fields.description: James Bond descends into mystery as he tries to stop a mysterious organisation from eliminating a country's most valuable resource.

fields.name: Stand By Me
fields.description: After the death of one of his friends, a writer recounts a childhood journey with his friends to find the body of a missing boy.

fields.name: Back To The Future 3
fields.description: Stranded in 1955, Marty McFly learns about the death of Doc Brown in 1885 and must travel back in time to save him. With no fuel readily available for the DeLorean, the two must figure how to escape the Old West before Emmett is murdered.

fields.name: Jumanji: The Next Level
fields.description: In Jumanji: The Next Level, the gang is back but the game has changed. As they return to rescue one of their own, the players will have to brave parts unknown from arid deserts to snowy mountains, to escape the world's most dangerous game.

fields.name: Beverly Hills Cop
fields.description: A freewheeling Detroit cop pursuing a murder investigation finds himself dealing with the very different culture of Beverly Hills.

fields.name: Ferris Bueller’s Day Off
fields.description: A high school wise guy is determined to have a day off from school, despite what the Principal thinks of that.

fields.name: American Graffiti
fields.description: A couple of high school grads spend one final night cruising the strip with their buddies before they go off to college.

fields.name: Happy Gilmore
fields.description: A rejected hockey player puts his skills to the golf course to save his grandmother's house.

fields.name: Grinch
fields.description: On the outskirts of Whoville lives a green, revenge-seeking Grinch who plans to ruin Christmas for all of the citizens of the town.

fields.name: Truman Show
fields.description: An insurance salesman discovers his whole life is actually a reality TV show.

fields.name: Naked Gun: From The Files Of Police Squad!
fields.description: Incompetent police Detective Frank Drebin must foil an attempt to assassinate Queen Elizabeth II.

fields.name: Hitch
fields.description: A smooth-talking man falls for a hardened columnist while helping a shy accountant woo a beautiful heiress.

fields.name: Mrs. Doubtfire
fields.description: After a bitter divorce, an actor disguises himself as a female housekeeper to spend time with his children held in custody by his former wife.

fields.name: Night At The Roxbury
fields.description: Two dim-witted brothers dream of owning their own dance club or at least getting into the coolest and most exclusive club in town, The Roxbury.

fields.name: Yes Man
fields.description: A man challenges himself to say "yes" to everything.

fields.name: Adventures Of Ford Fairlane
fields.description: A vulgar private detective is hired to find a missing groupie and is drawn into a mystery involving a series of murders tied to the music industry.

fields.name: Cable Guy
fields.description: A lonely and mentally disturbed cable guy raised on television just wants a new friend, but his target, a designer, rejects him, with bad consequences.

fields.name: Grumpy Old Men
fields.description: A lifelong feud between two neighbors since childhood only gets worse when a new female neighbor moves across the street.

fields.name: Motherless Brooklyn
fields.description: In 1950s New York, a lonely private detective afflicted with Tourette's Syndrome ventures to solve the murder of his mentor and only friend.

fields.name: American Gangster
fields.description: An outcast New York City cop is charged with bringing down Harlem drug lord Frank Lucas, whose real life inspired this partly biographical film.

fields.name: Die Hard with a Vengeance
fields.description: John McClane and a Harlem store owner are targeted by German terrorist Simon Gruber in New York City, where he plans to rob the Federal Reserve Building.

fields.name: Bourne Identity
fields.description: A man is picked up by a fishing boat, bullet-riddled and suffering from amnesia, before racing to elude assassins and attempting to regain his memory.

fields.name: Bourne Supremacy
fields.description: When Jason Bourne is framed for a CIA operation gone awry, he is forced to resume his former life as a trained assassin to survive.

fields.name: Bourne Ultimatum
fields.description: Jason Bourne dodges a ruthless C.I.A. official and his Agents from a new assassination program while searching for the origins of his life as a trained killer.

fields.name: Die Hard 2
fields.description: John McClane attempts to avert disaster as rogue military operatives seize control of Dulles International Airport in Washington, D.C.

fields.name: Dick Tracy
fields.description: The comic strip detective finds his life vastly complicated when Breathless Mahoney makes advances towards him while he is trying to battle Big Boy Caprice's united mob.

fields.name: Public Enemies
fields.description: The Feds try to take down notorious American gangsters John Dillinger, Baby Face Nelson and Pretty Boy Floyd during a booming crime wave in the 1930s.

fields.name: Taken
fields.description: A retired CIA agent travels across Europe and relies on his old skills to save his estranged daughter, who has been kidnapped while on a trip to Paris.

fields.name: Donnie Brasco
fields.description: An FBI undercover agent infiltrates the mob and finds himself identifying more with the mafia life, at the expense of his regular one.

fields.name: Casino
fields.description: A tale of greed, deception, money, power, and murder occur between two best friends: a mafia enforcer and a casino executive compete against each other over a gambling empire, and over a fast living and fast loving socialite.

fields.name: Parasite
fields.description: Greed and class discrimination threaten the newly formed symbiotic relationship between the wealthy Park family and the destitute Kim clan.

fields.name: Little Women
fields.description: Jo March reflects back and forth on her life, telling the beloved story of the March sisters - four young women, each determined to live life on her own terms.

fields.name: Pride and Prejudice
fields.description: Sparks fly when spirited Elizabeth Bennet meets single, rich, and proud Mr. Darcy. But Mr. Darcy reluctantly finds himself falling in love with a woman beneath his class. Can each overcome their own pride and prejudice?

fields.name: Eyes Wide Shut
fields.description: A New York City doctor embarks on a harrowing, night-long odyssey of sexual and moral discovery after his wife reveals a painful secret to him.

fields.name: Black Swan
fields.description: A committed dancer struggles to maintain her sanity after winning the lead role in a production of Tchaikovsky's "Swan Lake".

fields.name: Shutter Island
fields.description: In 1954, a U.S. Marshal investigates the disappearance of a murderer who escaped from a hospital for the criminally insane.

fields.name: Memento
fields.description: A man with short-term memory loss attempts to track down his wife's murderer.

fields.name: King Kong
fields.description: A greedy film producer assembles a team of moviemakers and sets out for the infamous Skull Island, where they find more than just cannibalistic natives.

fields.name: There Will Be Blood
fields.description: A story of family, religion, hatred, oil and madness, focusing on a turn-of-the-century prospector in the early days of the business.

fields.name: Prestige
fields.description: After a tragic accident, two stage magicians engage in a battle to create the ultimate illusion while sacrificing everything they have to outwit each other.

fields.name: Requiem For A Dream
fields.description: The drug-induced utopias of four Coney Island people are shattered when their addictions run deep.

fields.name: Westworld
fields.description: A robot malfunction creates havoc and terror for unsuspecting vacationers at a futuristic, adult-themed amusement park.

fields.name: Wild Bunch
fields.description: An aging group of outlaws look for one last big score as the "traditional" American West is disappearing around them.

fields.name: Last of the Mohicans
fields.description: Three trappers protect the daughters of a British Colonel in the midst of the French and Indian War.

fields.name: Dances with Wolves
fields.description: Lieutenant John Dunbar, assigned to a remote western Civil War outpost, befriends wolves and Indians, making him an intolerable aberration in the military.

fields.name: Alamo
fields.description: In 1836, a small band of soldiers sacrifice their lives in hopeless combat against a massive army in order to prevent a tyrant from smashing the new Republic of Texas.

fields.name: True Grit
fields.description: A drunken, hard-nosed U.S. Marshal and a Texas Ranger help a stubborn teenager track down her father's murderer in Indian Territory.

fields.name: Wyatt Earp
fields.description: The story of Wyatt Earp as he interacts and battles other famous figures of the Wild West era.

fields.name: Apache Gold
fields.description: When violent conflict breaks out between greedy railroaders and a tribe of Mescalero Apaches, only two men, destined to be blood brothers, can prevent all-out war: chief's son Winnetou and German engineer Old Shatterhand.

fields.name: Maverick
fields.description: Bret Maverick, needing money for a poker tournament, faces various comic mishaps and challenges, including a charming woman thief.

fields.name: True Grit
fields.description: A stubborn teenager enlists the help of a tough U.S. Marshal to track down her father's murderer.

fields.name: Rooster Cogburn
fields.description: Marshal Rooster Cogburn unwillingly teams up with Eula Goodnight to track down her father's murderers.

fields.name: Social Network
fields.description: As Harvard student Mark Zuckerberg creates the social networking site that would become known as Facebook, he is sued by the twins who claimed he stole their idea, and by the co-founder who was later squeezed out of the business.

fields.name: Apollo 13
fields.description: NASA must devise a strategy to return Apollo 13 to Earth safely after the spacecraft undergoes massive internal damage putting the lives of the three astronauts on board in jeopardy.

fields.name: Last Samurai
fields.description: An American military advisor embraces the Samurai culture he was hired to destroy after he is captured in battle.
King Leonidas of Sparta and a force of 300 men fight the Persians at Thermopylae in 480 B.C.

fields.name: JFK
fields.description: New Orleans District Attorney Jim Garrison discovers there's more to the Kennedy assassination than the official story.

fields.name: Braveheart
fields.description: Scottish warrior William Wallace leads his countrymen in a rebellion to free his homeland from the tyranny of King Edward I of England.

fields.name: Passion Of The Christ
fields.description: Depicts the final twelve hours in the life of Jesus of Nazareth, on the day of his crucifixion in Jerusalem.

fields.name: King Arthur
fields.description: A demystified take on the tale of King Arthur and the Knights of the Round Table.

fields.name: Windtalkers
fields.description: Two U.S. Marines in World War II are assigned to protect Navajo Marines, who use their native language as an unbreakable radio cypher.

fields.name: Hellraiser
fields.description: A woman discovers the newly resurrected, partially formed, body of her brother-in-law. She starts killing for him to revitalize his body so he can escape the demonic beings that are pursuing him after he escaped their sadistic underworld.

fields.name: Attack of the Crab Monsters
fields.description: Scientists become trapped on a shrinking island with intelligent, murderous giant crabs.

fields.name: Nightmare on Elm Street
fields.description: The spectre of a disfigured man haunts the children of the parents who murdered him, stalking and killing them in their dreams.

fields.name: Dracula
fields.description: In 1913, the charming, seductive and sinister vampire Count Dracula travels to England in search of an immortal bride.

fields.name: Candyman
fields.description: A "spiritual sequel" to the horror film Candyman (1992) that returns to the now-gentrified Chicago neighborhood where the legend began.

fields.name: Invisible Man
fields.description: When Cecilia's abusive ex takes his own life and leaves her his fortune, she suspects his death was a hoax. As a series of coincidences turn lethal, Cecilia works to prove that she is being hunted by someone nobody can see.

fields.name: Amityville Horror
fields.description: Newlyweds are terrorized by demonic forces after moving into a large house that was the site of a grisly mass murder a year before.

fields.name: Hostel
fields.description: Three backpackers head to a Slovak city that promises to meet their hedonistic expectations, with no idea of the hell that awaits them.

fields.name: Ring
fields.description: A journalist must investigate a mysterious videotape which seems to cause the death of anyone one week to the day after they view it.

fields.name: Spiral: Book of Saw
fields.description: A sadistic mastermind unleashes a twisted form of justice in Spiral, the terrifying new chapter from the book of Saw.

fields.name: Charlie And The Chocolate Factory
fields.description: A young boy wins a tour through the most magnificent chocolate factory in the world, led by the world's most unusual candy maker.

fields.name: Moulin Rouge
fields.description: A poet falls for a beautiful courtesan whom a jealous duke covets.

fields.name: Mamma Mia
fields.description: The story of a bride-to-be trying to find her real father told using hit songs by the popular 1970s group ABBA.

fields.name: Chicago
fields.description: Two death-row murderesses develop a fierce rivalry while competing for publicity, celebrity, and a sleazy lawyer's attention.

fields.name: Evita
fields.description: The hit musical based on the life of Evita Duarte, a B-picture Argentinian actress who eventually became the wife of Argentinian president Juan Perón, and the most beloved and hated woman in Argentina.

fields.name: Nine
fields.description: Famous film director Guido Contini struggles to find harmony in his professional and personal lives, as he engages in dramatic relationships with his wife, his mistress, his muse, his agent, and his mother.

fields.name: Phantom of the Opera
fields.description: An acid-scarred composer has his dwarf helper bring an opera singer to his London sewer hide-out.

fields.name: Maltese Falcon
fields.description: A private detective takes on a case that involves him with three eccentric criminals, a gorgeous liar, and their quest for a priceless statuette.

fields.name: Touch of Evil
fields.description: A stark, perverse story of murder, kidnapping, and police corruption in a Mexican border town.

fields.name: Sleeping City
fields.description: In New York, the murder of a Bellvue Hospital intern prompts the police to send an undercover detective to investigate.
